          <h1 class='playfair peach huge'>the idea</h1>
          <div class='columns three gradual'>
            <p><em>hum journal </em>is a publication designed to share and archive the creative work of visual artists and writers in the Greater Boston Area.  A small print publication that expands on its content and impact through an internet presence, we hope hum will further facilitate and expose a culture of beauty-production and  creative camaraderie in Boston. Hum seeks unconventional creative work; anything that is visually interesting, conceptual, or otherwise provocative.  You do not need to make "art" to submit, you just need to make "stuff."  Each issue will pose a theme that can be interpreted as abstractly or pointedly as the artist wishes.  hum journal is a publication designed to share and archive the creative work of journal is a publication designed to share and archive the creative work of visual artists and writers in the Greater Boston Area.  A small print publication that expands on its content and impact through an internet presence, we hope hum will further facilitate and expose a culture of beauty-production and creative camaraderie in Boston.	</p>
