          <div class='columns three blocks'>
            <p><em>two days apart</em> Holly and Anna were born apart in August. They met as rivals in a run for high school class historian. Then, some time later, they became friends. Now, they're amicably cohabitating in an apartment in Jamaica Plain.  </p>

            <p><em>anna leocha</em> is most amused by the moving image and has found inspiration in 60s/70s avant-garde cinema and the everyday intimacy of home videos. She likes to write. Proximity to the Atlantic Ocean and Walden Pond respectively is the best thing about living in Boston.  </p>

            <p><em>holly copeland</em> is a web producer and most interested in the anatomy of digital spaces and the creative design of interactive worlds. She's good with photoshop. Mi Pueblito restaurant in Eastie is the best thing about living in Boston. But shhh, don't tell anyone!</p>
